    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-10-21T10:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-10-21T10:15:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <head>269. Memorandum of a Conversation Between the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                        State</gloss> and the Under Secretary of State (<persName corresp="#p_HHJ1"
                        type="to">Hoover</persName>), Department of State, Washington, October 21,
                    1957, 11:15 a.m.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d269fn1">Source: <persName
                            corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> Papers, General Memoranda of
                        Conversation. Confidential; Personal and Private. Drafted by
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1957-10-21T11:15:00-04:00"
                            >October 21, 1957, 11:15 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName> said that he had a talk with
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_ARB1">Anderson</persName> wherein the latter had
                    put out the idea that some sort of an international Mid East organization might
                    be established which would receive a tax of 10% which Western companies
                    receiving Middle East oil would impose and which organization with joint
                    Arab-West management would use the funds for economic development in the Middle
                    East.</p>
                <p>I said I thought this idea was very interesting and hoped that he could work on
                    it. Later on I saw Secretary <persName corresp="#p_ARB1">Anderson</persName> and
                    expressed the same thought to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">JFD</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
